data.title: Dean Tennant Rides Sooke’s No Fall Zone
data.meta_description: Join NOBL athlete and Van Isle freeride legend Dean Tennant as he rides the infamous Sooke Flow Line. Breathe, balance and whatever you do, don’t look down!
data.text: The Sooke Flow Line falls firmly into the double black feature category. This old piece of concrete pipe was originally used to transport water from Sooke all the way to Victoria, about 38km (23 miles) away. While you can’t ride the entire thing, there’s a decent bit of fun to be had if you’re a daredevil, and NOBL athlete and local freeride legend Dean Tennant is definitely brave enough to ride it.
